# Operator Precedence

When you combine multiple operators in a single line, JavaScript needs rules to decide which ones to calculate first. This is called **Operator Precedence**.

Just like in math class (PEMDAS / BODMAS), some operations are more important than others.

```javascript
let math = 5 + 3 * 2;
// Does it do 5+3 first? (8 * 2 = 16)
// Or does it do 3*2 first? (5 + 6 = 11)
```

JavaScript multiplies first! The answer is 11.

slides.codeSnippet:
// Normal math handles division first
console.log(10 + 20 / 2); // 20

// Parentheses force addition first
console.log((10 + 20) / 2); // 15
